'''[[half]]-[[life]]'''
#{{mathematics}} For a [[quantity]] subject to [[exponential]] [[decay]], the time required for the quantity to fall to half its [[initial]] [[value]].
#{{physics}} The time required for half of the [[nuclei]] in a [[sample]] of a [[specific]] [[isotope]] to undergo [[radioactive]] [[decay]]. Note: this is a [[statistical]] measure - you cannot tell when any individual nucleus will decay.

